MANCHESTER UNITED FC has sacked coach Jose Mourinho. This follows his disastrous start to the season. Mourinho’s last game was on Sunday, when Man United was whipped 3-1 by Liverpool. Manchester United is now number sixth in the table. Mail Online reports that Mourinho will get a £22.5m pay-off as club remain in the Champions League. The publication said that the Portuguese was pictured being driven into Carrington minutes before sacking. A 65-word statement revealed that a caretaker coach will take charge until summer. Zinedine Zidane and Mauricio Pochettino are among the leading candidates to replace him, while assistant coach Michael Carrick would be a popular choice to step in as caretaker manager.